     <p>
    The 
    <xr pageref="N" ref="SI.IS.1">Republic of Slovenia</xr>
     is situated in south-central Europe. Constitutional amendments approved in 1989 confirmed Slovenia's sovereignty and its right to secede from the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia (SFRY). In 1990 Slovenia was redesignated the Republic of Slovenia and the Republic's sovereignty was declared. In June 1991 Slovenia and Croatia declared their independence from the SFRY. Serbian-dominated federal troops were mobilized and sporadic fighting ensued. Following the implementation of a ceasefire, Slovenia proclaimed its full independence in October. Ljubljana is the capital. The official language is Slovene, and in ethnically mixed regions also Hungarian and Italian. Slovenia acceded to the European Union in 2004, and adopted the euro in 2007.
  </p>
